{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"spiny-ferry-ripen","description":"## Summary\n`rebar list --status=all` (or any invalid status value) silently returns an empty list instead of rejecting the value. An unrecognized filter value should be a loud error, not an empty result set.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. Run `rebar list --status=all` (all is not a valid status).\n2. Observe: exit 0, output `[]`.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n- Expected: non-zero exit + error naming the invalid status value and listing valid ones (open/in_progress/closed/blocked/deleted...).\n- Actual: exit 0 with [] — indistinguishable from 'no tickets match'.\n\n## Impact\nCorrupted a real measurement during the 3006-e198 derisk experiments (an agent computed 614 false class-A drift candidates from the silently-empty list). Any agent or script filtering by a mistyped status silently operates on an empty world.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] An invalid --status value exits non-zero with an error listing valid statuses.\n- [ ] A test covers the invalid-status path (RED before fix).\n- [ ] Valid statuses (and any 'all'-equivalent, if one is intended) are documented in `rebar list --help`.","id":"2dce-d7b9-6574-4f62","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"rebar list --status=<invalid> silently returns empty instead of erroring"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783105223495646001,"uuid":"2ab83683-9fd1-4464-9764-a43ffbf353ce"}